                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d224">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6005: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-09T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 9, 1933—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 9—12:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>226. Reuter reports from Nanking and Tokyo yesterday that both the Chinese
                    Government and the Manchukuo authorities have issued mandates depriving General
                    Tang Yu-lin, former chairman of Jehol of all his civil and military posts.
                    Nanking has also ordered his arrest and punishment for desertion.</p>
                <p>Manchukuo has appointed General Chang Hai-peng Governor of Jehol.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
